\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} (1+\cos x)^{\tan x}
y=(1+\cos x)^{\tan x} \implies \log y=\tan x \log(1+\cos x)
\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}}\log y=\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}}[\tan x\log(1+\cos x)]=\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}}\frac{\log(1+\cos x)}{\cos x} \times \lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \sin x
=\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{(-\sin x)}{(1+\cos x)(-\sin x)}=\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{1}{1+\cos x}=1
\implies\log\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}}(1+\cos x)^{\tan x}=1
\implies\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}}(1+\cos x)^{\tan x}=e
"e"
"e^{-1}"
y=\lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} (1+\cos x)^{\tan x}
\ln y=\ln \lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} (1+\cos x)^{\tan x} \\ \ln y= \lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \ln(1+\cos x)^{\tan x} \\ \ln y= \lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \tan x\cdot\ln(1+\cos x) \\ \ln y= \lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{\ln(1+\cos x)}{\cot x} \\ \ln y= \lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{\frac{-\sin x}{(1+\cos x)}}{-\csc^2 x} \\ \ln y= \lim_{x \to \frac{\pi}{2}} \frac{\sin^3 x}{(1+\cos x)}=1 \\ \implies y=e 
